s, Eric Harris\u2014carrying a carbine rifle and a sawed-off pump-action shotgun\u2014and Dylan Klebold\u2014carrying a TEC-9 pistol and a sawed-off 12 gauge double-barreled shotgun\u2014shot and killed 12 students and a teacher, and injured 21 other students and a teacher at [[Columbine High School]]. Two more students and a teacher were injured escaping. Ten of the 12 students killed were shot at nearly [[point-blank range]] while hiding under tables in the school library in seven minutes by the two shooters. Both were armed with numerous [[pipe bomb]]s, [[napalm]], knives, and other homemade explosives. Two propane [[time bomb]]s (which only one partially detonated) were set in the school cafeteria. After their rampage, Harris and Klebold died of self-inflicted gunshot wounds to the head. Both are believed to have committed suicide simultaneously and both bodies were found in the back of the library together. Columbine High School is located in the [[Columbine, Colorado|Columbine]] CDP of Jefferson County, near the cities of [[Denver]] and [[Littleton, Colorado|Littleton]]. Harris and Klebold were both victims of [[School bullying|bullying]]. \n|-\n| April 28, 1999\n| [[Taber, Alberta]], Canada\n| [[Todd Cameron Smith]], 14\n| 1 dead\n| 1 injured\n| [[W. R. Myers High School shooting]]. 14-year-old Todd Cameron Smith brought a sawn-off .22-caliber rifle to W.R Myers High School and shot two students, killing one, Cameron served a 3 year jail sentence and lived seven years on probation.\n|-\n| May 20, 1999\n| [[Conyers, Georgia]], United States\n| T.J. Solomon, 15\n|\n| 6 injured\n| 15-year-old T.J. Solomon, armed with a .22-caliber rifle and a handgun, opened fire at Heritage High School, wounding six students.\n|-\n| July 29, 1999\n| [[Soweto]], South Africa\n| Charles Raboroko, 39\n| 3 dead\n|\n| Teacher Charles Raboroko shot and killed three of his colleagues in the staffroom at Anchor Comprehensive High School in Soweto. When he tried to escape he was hindered by angry students outside the school, whereupon he hid in a classroom, where he was later arrested by police. Raboroko was said to have borne a grudge against one of his victims, Henry Lebea, whom he killed with five shots in the head.<ref>[http://www.iol.co.za/index.php?set_id=1&click_id=105&art_id=ct19990729210710566T260721 Teacher's wife knew colleague would kill], ''[[Independent Online (South Africa)|Independent Online]]'' (July 29, 1999)</ref><ref>[http://www.iol.co.za/index.php?set_id=1&click_id=105&art_id=ct1999073010225773T260477 School shooting 'like a horror movie' ], ''[[Independent Online (South Africa)|Independent Online]]'' (July 30, 1999)</ref>\n|-\n| August 11, 1999\n| [[Sekinchan]], [[Malaysia]]\n| Na Teck Ker, 42\n|\n| 6 injured\n| After he had been humiliated by friends, Na Teck Ker, a 42-year-old fisherman, bought a [[Parang (knife)|parang]] and headed for Sekolah Menengah Kebangsaan Yoke Kuan in Sekinchan, where he set his motorcycle ablaze, before chasing and randomly attacking students. When he was finally overpowered by teachers and passers-by he had already injured six pupils. Na Teck Ker was handed over to police and sentenced to 42 months in jail.<ref>[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=lnAWAAAAIBAJ&sjid=rRQEAAAAIBAJ&pg=6863,3882082&dq= Man with parang injures six pupils], ''[[New Straits Times]]'' (August 12, 1999)</ref><ref>Amok who slashed pupils jailed 42 months, ''[[New Straits Times]]'' (October 13, 1999)</ref>\n|-\n| October 19, 1999\n| [[Longzhou County]], China\n| Liang Yongcheng, 30\n| 1 dead\n| 7 injured\n| After spending the afternoon drinking, school guard Liang Yongcheng walked into a students' dormitory at a middle school in Longzhou county and threatened to kill everybody who tried to stop him. He eventually committed suicide, but not before shooting a teacher and six students with a hunting rifle.<ref>[https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/thestar/access/445517051.html?dids=445517051:445517051&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Oct+26%2C+1999&author=&pub=Daily+Mercury&desc=School+guard+injures+seven+in+shooting+spree&pqatl=google School guard injures seven in shooting spree], ''[[Guelph Mercury]]'' (October 26, 1999)</ref>\n|-\n| October 20, 1999\n| [[Houston, Texas]], United States\n| Estanislao Balderas, 14\n| 1 dead\n|\n| Estanislao Balderas stabbed a 13-year-old boy named Samuel Avila in the head with a screwdriver in a fight at Deady Middle School. Samuel Avila died. Balderas was arrested and prosecuted.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.leagle.com/decision/2003593349F3d244_1569.xml/RIVERA+v.+HOUSTON+INDEPENDENT+SCHOOL+DIST.|title=RIVERA v. HOUSTON INDEPEN \u2013 349 F.3d 244 (2003) \u2013 9f3d2441569 \u2013 Leagle.com|website=leagle.com}}</ref>\n|-\n| November 9, 1999\n| [[Mei\u00dfen]], Germany\n| Andreas S., 15\n| 1 dead\n|\n| A masked student, who was only identified as Andreas S., fatally stabbed teacher Sigrun Leuteritz 22 times with a kitchen knife in front of his classmates, before trying to escape. The student was later arrested and sentenced to 7\u00bd years in prison.<ref>[http://www.spiegel.de/panorama/0,1518,78666,00.html Mord an Lehrerin \u2013 Lange Jugendstrafe f\u00fcr 15-J\u00e4hrigen], ''[[Spiegel Online]]'' (May 29, 2000)</ref>\n|-\n| November 19, 1999\n| [[Deming, New Mexico]], United States\n| Victor Cordova, Jr., 12\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 12-year-old Victor Cordova Jr. dressed in camouflage and shot 13-year-old Araceli Tena. Tena died a day later from sustained wounds in life support.<ref>[http://lubbockonline.com/stories/112199/reg_112199054.shtml 13-year-old New Mexico student kills girl in school shooting], ''[[Lubbock Avalanche-Journal]]'' (November 21, 1999)</ref>\n|-\n| December 6, 1999\n| [[Fort Gibson, Oklahoma]], United States\n| Seth Trickey, 13\n|\n| 4 injured\n| 13-year-old Seth Trickey armed himself with a 9&nbsp;mm semiautomatic handgun and opened fire of 15 rounds at Fort Gibson Middle School, injuring four classmates.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www2.ljworld.com/news/2003/sep/26/school_shooter_may/|title=School shooter may end up in Lawrence|work=[[Lawrence Journal-World]]|date=26 September 2003}}</ref>\n|-\n| December 7, 1999\n| [[Veghel]], Netherlands\n| Ali D\u00fczg\u00fcn, 17\n|\n| 5 injured\n| 17-year-old Ali D\u00fczg\u00fcn, of [[Turkish Kurdistan|Turkish Kurdish]] origin, shot and injured five people at a school. He claimed he wanted to avenge the family honour by shooting his sister's boyfriend, who he believed had brought the family honour to disgrace. The boyfriend, three other students and a teacher were injured in the shooting. D\u00fczg\u00fcn was sentenced to five years in prison, his father was sentenced to eight years.\n|}\n\n===2000s===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:90%;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:65px;\"| Date\n! style=\"width:85px;\"| Location\n! style=\"width:75px;\"| Attacker(s)\n! data-sort-type=\"number\" style=\"width:75px;\"| Dead{{r|group=lower-alpha|note_a}}\n! data-sort-type=\"number\" style=\"width:75px;\"| Injured{{r|group=lower-alpha|note_a}}\n! Description\n|-\n| March 16, 2000\n| [[Brannenburg]], [[Bavaria]], Germany\n| Michael F., 16\n| 1 dead\n| 1 injured\n| A 16-year-old student fatally shot a teacher and then shot himself in a suicide attempt, and has been in a [[coma]] ever since.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.spiegel.de/panorama/justiz/0,1518,449549,00.html|title = Massenmorde in der Schule|publisher= www.spiegel.de }}</ref>\n|-\n| April 20, 2000\n| [[Ottawa]], [[Ontario]], Canada\n| ..., 15\n|\n| 5 injured\n| A 15-year-old student at [[Cairine Wilson Secondary School]] in the suburban community of [[Orleans, Ontario|Orleans]] pulled out a knife and stabbed a fellow student whom he was conversing with, and then ran through the school stabbing another three students and a teacher's aide. Michael Jordan, the school principal finally convinced the youth to surrender the weapon.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cbc.ca/canada/story/2000/04/22/stabbingcharges000422.html |archive-url=https://archive.today/20120722075250/http://www.cbc.ca/canada/story/2000/04/22/stabbingcharges000422.html |archive-date=2012-07-22 |title=Boy charged with Ontario school stabbing |publisher=Cbc.ca |date=2000-11-11 |accessdate=2011-03-12 |url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|-\n| May 26, 2000\n| [[Lake Worth, Florida]], United States\n| [[Nathaniel Brazill]], 13\n| 1 dead\n|\n| One teacher, Barry Grunow, had been shot and killed at Lake Worth Middle School by 13-year-old Nate Brazill with .25-caliber semiautomatic pistol on the last day of classes. Brazill was convicted of the murder and sentenced to twenty-five years in prison.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/US/story?id=93260&page=1|title=Brazill Guilty of Second-Degree Murder|first=A. B. C.|last=News|date=7 January 2006|website=ABC News}}</ref>\n|-\n| September 26, 2000\n| [[New Orleans, Louisiana]], United States\n| \n| \n| 2 injured\n| Darrel Johnson, 13, and Alfred Anderson were initially charged with [[Louisiana]] attempted second degree murder in a school shooting where both were shot with the same gun.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Jury Is Still Out|url=http://www.bestofneworleans.com/gambit/the-jury-is-still-out/Content?oid=1239849|date=January 8, 2002}}</ref>\n|-\n| October 19, 2000\n| [[New York City, New York]], United States\n| Rickley Gregoire, 16<br>Eduardo Hall, 16\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 12-year-old Anthony Haynes is stabbed to death in the cafeteria of [[Canarsie High School]]. Two 16-year-old students were arrested for the crime. It was suspected that the stabbing was gang-related.<ref>{{cite news|last=Gootman |first=Elissa |url=https://select.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=F70C15FC3B5A0C738EDDA90994D8404482 |title=Boy Is Stabbed in Brooklyn After School-Cafeteria Fight |location=New York City |publisher=Select.nytimes.com |date=2000-10-20 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| October 23, 2000\n| [[Los Angeles, California]], United States\n|\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 20-year-old security guard Re