ice.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.ca/newspapers?id=nUouAAAAIBAJ&sjid=tX4FAAAAIBAJ&pg=6854,2114367&dq=school+tragedy&hl=en |title=Shot By Schoolmate Frontenac School, Kingston, Scene of a Tragedy. Boy Killed Girl Pupil |publisher=News.google.ca |date=1902-04-29 |accessdate=2017-10-18}}</ref>\n|-\n| February 24, 1903\n| [[Inman, South Carolina]], United States\n| Reuben Pitts\n| 1 dead\n| \n| Edward Foster, a 17-year-old student at Inman High school, was shot and fatally wounded by his teacher Reuben Pitts after he tried to resist punishment. Pitts said the student struck the pistol, which he drew in self-defense, and it fired. Pitts was acquitted of murder.<ref>[https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/ajc_historic/access/559912722.html?dids=559912722:559912722&FMT=CITE&FMTS=CITE:AI&date=Feb+25%2C+1903&author=&pub=The+Atlanta+Constitution&desc=CAROLINA+YOUTH+SHOT+BY+TEACHER&pqatl=google Carolina youth shot by teacher], ''[[The Atlanta Constitution]]'' (February 25, 1903)</ref><ref>[https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/ajc_historic/access/560490212.html?dids=560490212:560490212&FMT=CITE&FMTS=CITE:AI&date=Sep+20%2C+1903&author=&pub=The+Atlanta+Constitution&desc=REUBEN+PITTS+GETS+FREEDOM&pqatl=google Reuben Pitts gets freedom], ''[[The Atlanta Constitution]]'' (September 20, 1903)</ref>\n|-\n|July 21, 1903\n|[[Jackson, Kentucky]], United States\n|\n| 2 dead\n| 1 injured\n|At Cave Run School, James Barrett and Mack Howard fought a duel with pistols over a card game, killing each other. Another student James Vires, aged 12, suffered a wound while sitting at his desk.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://cdnc.ucr.edu/cdnc/cgi-bin/cdnc?a=d&cl=search&d=LAH19030722.2.14&srpos=1&e=20-07-1903-22-07-1903--en--20-LAH-1--txt-IN-barrett----|work=Los Angeles Herald, Volume XXX, Number 288|title=Deulists Fatally Shot|date=22 July 1903}}</ref>\n|-\n|April 6, 1904\n|[[Chicago]], [[Illinois]], United States\n| Henry Schaze\n|1 dead\n|\n|Two students had been fighting over a girl for the better part of a year. Finally, Henry Schaze pushed 16-year-old Paul Jelick to the ground and shot him dead.<ref>''San Francisco Call,'' Volume 95, Number 129, 7 April 1904</ref>\n|-\n|November 16, 1904\n|[[Riverside, California]], United States\n|\n| 2 dead\n| 1 injured\n|At Indian School, a gun fight broke out between pupils. Charles Colby was shot in the head, then returned fire, killing Tom Bucanoros and fatally wounding Fred Smith.<ref>''San Francisco Call,'' Volume 96, Number 170, 17 November 1904</ref>\n|-\n|December 16, 1904\n|[[Magee, Mississippi]], United States\n| E. E. Mangum\n|1 dead\n|1 injured\n|E. E. Mangum was shot through the head and killed by the principal of the high school, Professor J. E. Woodward, after the student argued about punishment of his son and the argument became violent.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://cdnc.ucr.edu/cdnc/cgi-bin/cdnc?a=d&cl=search&d=SFC19041217.2.76.22&srpos=1&e=15-12-1904-17-12-1904--en--20-SFC-1--txt-IN-mangum----|work=San Francisco Call, Volume 97, Number 17|title=High School Principal Shoots Irate Parent|date=17 December 1904}}</ref>\n|-\n|February 9, 1905\n|[[Colusa, California]], United States\n|William Ingrim\n| \n|2 injured\n|At the request of his childhood friend, Pearl Cruse, Elmer Hildreth - a 17-year-old non-student, attended a meeting between Miss Cruse and her teacher. This meeting ended ended in \"a hand to hand\" encounter between the teacher and Cruse. Hildreth became involved in a physical confrontation with school trustee Ingrim, whom he shot. He was found to have acted in self-defense. Ingrim survived the shooting.<ref>''Colusa Sun Herald'' 15 February 1905</ref>\n|-\n| September 12, 1905\n| [[Athens, Tennessee]], United States\n| Ernest Powers, 15\n| 1 dead\n| \n| 15-year-old student Ernest Powers fatally stabbed his teacher Elbert Wattanbarger, when he attempted to whip him for throwing stones.<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/1905/09/17/archives/surrender-boy-who-slew-teacher.html Surrender Boy Who Slew Teacher], ''The N