e students\n| 2 dead\n|\n| Three 12- and 13-year-old students strangled an 8-year-old boy and his 5-year-old brother to death at a boarding school in hope the school would close down, so they would get a day off.<ref>[https://www.usatoday.com/news/world/2007-08-25-india_N.htm Indian police say 3 children killed 2 others], ''[[USA Today]]'' (August 25, 2007)</ref>\n|-\n| September 11, 2007\n| [[Toronto]],<br>[[Ontario]],<br>Canada\n| Unknown\n| 1 dead\n|\n| Dineshkumar Murugiah, a 16-year-old student, was fatally stabbed in an alleyway siding [[Winston Churchill Collegiate Institute]], in the [[Scarborough, Toronto|Scarborough]] part of [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]]. Murugiah was on lunch break during the stabbing, which occurred around 12:05&nbsp;p.m. local time.<ref name=\"torontostar912\">{{cite news|first= Tamara| last= Cherry| title=Dineshkumar Murugiah \u2013 Slain student identified|date=2007-09-12|url =https://www.thestar.com/article/255762|work=[[The Toronto Star]]|accessdate = 2009-06-10}}</ref><ref name=\"cbc913\">{{cite news|title=Dineshkumar Murugiah-Victim in high school murder was 'going for lunch |date=2007-09-13 |publisher=[[CBC News]] |url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/toronto/victim-in-high-school-murder-was-going-for-lunch-1.668220 |accessdate=2009-06-10 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090724115200/https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/toronto/victim-in-high-school-murder-was-going-for-lunch-1.668220 |archivedate=July 24, 2009 }}</ref> No suspects were ever sought in the stabbing.\n|-\n| September 28, 2007\n| [[Oroville, California|Oroville]],<br>[[California]],<br>United States\n| Greg Dean Wright, 17\n|\n| \n| 17-year-old student Greg Wright [[n:Hostage situation at California high school ends peacefully|held twenty-seven students and a teacher hostage]] in a classroom at [[Oroville, California#Oroville Union High School District|Las Plumas High School]], in [[Oroville, California]], for about two hours before surrendering to law