{"title_page": "Kolusu Parthasarathy", "text_new": "{{Hatnote|This is a [[Telugu language|Telugu name]]; the family name is ''Kolusu''.}}\n{{short description|Indian politician}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=August 2016}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2018}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name             = Kolusu Parthasarathy\n| honorific_prefix = <!-- Shri -->\n| honorific_suffix = \n| image            = Kolusu Parthasarathy.jpg\n| caption          = \n| party            = [[YSR Congress Party]]  (2014-present)<br>[[Indian National Congress]] (until 2014)\n| office1          = Member of the [[Andhra Pradesh Legislative Assembly]] for [[Penamaluru (Assembly constituency)|Penamaluru]]\n| order1           = \n| predecessor1     = [[Bode Prasad]]\n| successor1       = \n| birth_date       = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1965|4|18}}\n| birth_place      = [[Karakampadu]], [[Andhra Pradesh State]], [[India]]\n| death_date       = \n| death_place      = \n| spouse           = Smt. K. Kamala Lakshmi\n| children         = K.Nikhil Krishna (1 Son)\n| residence        = [[Vijayawada, Andhra Pradesh]], [[India]] <BR>[[Hyderabad, Telangana]], [[India]]\n| term_start1      = 2019\n| term_end1        = \n| term_start2      = 2009\n| term_end2        = 2014\n| successor2       = [[Bode Prasad]]\n| office3          = Member of the [[Andhra Pradesh Legislative Assembly]] for Vuyyur Assembly Constituency\n| term_start3      = 2004\n| term_end3        = 2009\n| predecessor3     = Chalasani Pandu\n| order3           = \n| father           = [[Kolusu Pedareddaiah Yadav]]\n}}\n'''Kolusu Parthasarathy''' (born 18 April 1965) is an Indian politician. He represents the YSRCP from Penamaluru Assembly Constituency, [[Krishna District]] of [[Andhra Pradesh]]. He was elected to the Andhra Pradesh Legislative Assembly for three terms, in 2004, 2009 and 2019. Elected first in 2004 from the Vuyyur Constituency, and then in 2009 and 2019 elected from the Penamaluru Constituency. He is the president of the Krishna District [[YSR Congress Party]]. \n\nHe served as Minister for Animal Husbandry, Dairy Development, Fisheries and Veterinary University in the cabinet of Y.S. Rajasekhar Reddy. Pardha Saradhy was allotted the portfolio of Secondary Education, Govt.Exminations, and Intermediate Education. He was the last Minister for Secondary Education for united Andhra Pradesh.\n\n== Early life  ==\nParthasarathy was born in 18 April 1965 at Karakampadu, [[Krishna district]], [[Andhra Pradesh]] in an political family. His father [[Kolusu Pedareddaiah Yadav]] is an politician and in 1991 and 1996 was elected as Member of [[Machilipatnam (Lok Sabha constituency)|Machilipatnam]] lok sabha Constituency.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elections.in/andhra-pradesh/parliamentary-constituencies/machilipatnam.html|title=Machilipatnam (Andhra Pradesh) Lok Sabha Election Results 2019 - Parliamentary Constituency|website=www.elections.in}}</ref> His mother was a housewife.\n\n== Career ==\nAs a member of the [[Indian National Congress|Indian National Congress(INC)]] party, he was elected as an MLA for the first time in 2004 elections from Vuyyur Assembly Constituency. He is the last MLA from Vuyyur Assembly Constituency. He served as Minister for Animal Husbandry, Dairy Development, Fisheries and Veterinary University in the cabinet of Y. S. Rajasekhar Reddy and continued with the same ministry in K. Rosaiah's team. Parthasarathy was elected to Assembly from Penamaluru Constituency for the second term in the 2009 elections, after reorganisation of the constituencies. In the re-formation of the cabinet by N. Kiran Kumar Reddy, Saradhy was allotted the portfolio of Secondary Education, Govt.Exminations, AP. Residential Educational Institutions Society, Hyderabad Public School and Intermediate Education. He was the last Minister for Secondary Education for united Andhra Pradesh.<ref>[https://www.indiatoday.in/india/south/story/andhra-minister-k.-parthasarathy-keeps-class-x-results-on-hold-103145-2012-05-24 ''India Today''].</ref> When INC divided AP into Andhra Pradesh and [[Telangana]] he resigned from the INC and played a major role in Samaikyandhra movement in Krishan District leaders.\n\nIn 2014 Parthasarathy joined [[YSR Congress Party]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thehansindia.com/posts/index/General-Elections/2014-04-13/Parthasarathy-Vedavyas-join-YSRCP/91938|title=Parthasarathy, Vedavyas join YSRCP|first=Our|last=Bureau|date=13 April 2014|website=www.thehansindia.com}}</ref> He left Penamaluru and he lost the race for the Machilipatnam Constituency in 2014. He is the working president of YSR Congress Party for [[Krishna District]]. Sarathy was fighting for [[Special Status for Andhra Pradesh Protests|Special Status for A.P]]. He brought all party's leaders of Krishna District onto one platform on the issue of Special Status. In the 2019 general election he contested as Member of the [[Andhra Pradesh Legislative Assembly]] for [[Penamaluru (Assembly constituency)|Penamaluru]] and he won with majority of 11,317 over the incumbent Bode Prasad.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://epaper.sakshi.com/2167348/Krishna-District/24-05-2019#page/1/2|title=Sakshi Telugu Daily Krishna District epaper dated Fri, 24 May 19|website=epaper.sakshi.com}}</ref>\n\n== Achievements ==\n* He was elected as an MLA for the first time in 2004 elections from Vuyyur Assembly Constituency, He is the last MLA for Vuyyur.\n* He served as Minister for Animal Husbandry for the combined state of Andhra Pradesh. \n* He is the last Minister for Secondary Education for the combined state of Andhra Pradesh.\n* He won every time when he contested as Member of Legislative Assembly.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Chalasani Pandu]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[List of Member of the Andhra Pradesh Legislative Assembly for Penamaluru (Assembly constituency)|MLA Penamaluru]]|years=2004\u20132014}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Bode Prasad]]}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Bode Prasad]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[List of Member of the Andhra Pradesh Legislative Assembly for Penamaluru (Assembly constituency)|MLA Penamaluru]]|years=2019}}\n{{s-end}}\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-inc}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Parthasarathy, Kolusu}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Telugu politicians]]\n[[Category:People from Krishna district]]\n[[Category:YSR Congress Party]]\n[[Category:1965 births]]\n", "text_old": "{{Hatnote|This is a [[Telugu language|Telugu name]]; the family name is ''Kolusu''.}}\n{{short description|Indian politician}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=August 2016}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2018}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name             = Kolusu Parthasarathy\n| honorific_prefix = <!-- Shri -->\n| honorific_suffix = \n| image            = Kolusu Parthasarathy.jpg\n| caption          = \n| party            = [[YSR Congress Party]]  (2014-present)<br>[[Indian National Congress]] (until 2014)\n| office1          = Member of the [[Andhra Pradesh Legislative Assembly]] for [[Penamaluru (Assembly constituency)|Penamaluru]]\n| order1           = \n| predecessor1     = [[Bode Prasad]]\n| successor1       = \n| birth_date       = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1965|4|18}}\n| birth_place      = [[Karakampadu]], [[Andhra Pradesh State]], [[India]]\n| death_date       = \n| death_place      = \n| spouse           = Smt. K. Kamala Lakshmi\n| children         = K.Nikhil Krishna (1 Son)\n| residence        = [[Vijayawada, Andhra Pradesh]], [[India]] <BR>[[Hyderabad, Telangana]], [[India]]\n| term_start1      = 2019\n| term_end1        = \n| term_start2      = 2009\n| term_end2        = 2014\n| successor2       = [[Bode Prasad]]\n| office3          = Member of the [[Andhra Pradesh Legislative Assembly]] for Vuyyur Assembly Constituency\n| term_start3      = 2004\n| term_end3        = 2009\n| predecessor3     = Chalasani Pandu\n| order3           = \n| father           = [[Kolusu Pedareddaiah Yadav]]\n}}\n'''Kolusu Parthasarathy''' (born 18 April 1965) is an Indian politician. He represents the YSRCP from Penamaluru Assembly Constituency, [[Krishna District]] of [[Andhra Pradesh]]. He was elected to the Andhra Pradesh Legislative Assembly for three terms, in 2004, 2009 and 2019. Elected first in 2004 from the Vuyyur Constituency, and then in 2009 and 2019 elected from the Penamaluru Constituency. He is the president of the Krishna District [[YSR Congress Party]]. \n\nHe served as Minister for Animal Husbandry, Dairy Development, Fisheries and Veterinary University in the cabinet of Y.S. Rajasekhar Reddy. Pardha Saradhy was allotted the portfolio of Secondary Education, Govt.Exminations, and Intermediate Education. He was the last Minister for Secondary Education for united Andhra Pradesh.\n\n== Early life  ==\nParthasarathy was born in 18 April 1965 at Karakampadu, [[Krishna district]], [[Andhra Pradesh]] in an political family. His father, \tKolusu Pedareddaiah Yadav, is an politician and in 1991 and 1996 was elected as Member of [[Machilipatnam (Lok Sabha constituency)|Machilipatnam]] lok sabha Constituency.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elections.in/andhra-pradesh/parliamentary-constituencies/machilipatnam.html|title=Machilipatnam (Andhra Pradesh) Lok Sabha Election Results 2019 - Parliamentary Constituency|website=www.elections.in}}</ref> His mother was a housewife.\n\n== Career ==\nAs a member of the [[Indian National Congress|Indian National Congress(INC)]] party, he was elected as an MLA for the first time in 2004 elections from Vuyyur Assembly Constituency. He is the last MLA from Vuyyur Assembly Constituency. He served as Minister for Animal Husbandry, Dairy Development, Fisheries and Veterinary University in the cabinet of Y. S. Rajasekhar Reddy and continued with the same ministry in K. Rosaiah's team. Parthasarathy was elected to Assembly from Penamaluru Constituency for the second term in the 2009 elections, after reorganisation of the constituencies. In the re-formation of the cabinet by N. Kiran Kumar Reddy, Saradhy was allotted the portfolio of Secondary Education, Govt.Exminations, AP. Residential Educational Institutions Society, Hyderabad Public School and Intermediate Education. He was the last Minister for Secondary Education for united Andhra Pradesh.<ref>[https://www.indiatoday.in/india/south/story/andhra-minister-k.-parthasarathy-keeps-class-x-results-on-hold-103145-2012-05-24 ''India Today''].</ref> When INC divided AP into Andhra Pradesh and [[Telangana]] he resigned from the INC and played a major role in Samaikyandhra movement in Krishan District leaders.\n\nIn 2014 Parthasarathy joined [[YSR Congress Party]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thehansindia.com/posts/index/General-Elections/2014-04-13/Parthasarathy-Vedavyas-join-YSRCP/91938|title=Parthasarathy, Vedavyas join YSRCP|first=Our|last=Bureau|date=13 April 2014|website=www.thehansindia.com}}</ref> He left Penamaluru and he lost the race for the Machilipatnam Constituency in 2014. He is the working president of YSR Congress Party for [[Krishna District]]. Sarathy was fighting for [[Special Status for Andhra Pradesh Protests|Special Status for A.P]]. He brought all party's leaders of Krishna District onto one platform on the issue of Special Status. In the 2019 general election he contested as Member of the [[Andhra Pradesh Legislative Assembly]] for [[Penamaluru (Assembly constituency)|Penamaluru]] and he won with majority of 11,317 over the incumbent Bode Prasad.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://epaper.sakshi.com/2167348/Krishna-District/24-05-2019#page/1/2|title=Sakshi Telugu Daily Krishna District epaper dated Fri, 24 May 19|website=epaper.sakshi.com}}</ref>\n\n== Achievements ==\n* He was elected as an MLA for the first time in 2004 elections from Vuyyur Assembly Constituency, He is the last MLA for Vuyyur.\n* He served as Minister for Animal Husbandry for the combined state of Andhra Pradesh. \n* He is the last Minister for Secondary Education for the combined state of Andhra Pradesh.\n* He won every time when he contested as Member of Legislative Assembly.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Chalasani Pandu]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[List of Member of the Andhra Pradesh Legislative Assembly for Penamaluru (Assembly constituency)|MLA Penamaluru]]|years=2004\u20132014}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Bode Prasad]]}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Bode Prasad]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[List of Member of the Andhra Pradesh Legislative Assembly for Penamaluru (Assembly constituency)|MLA Penamaluru]]|years=2019}}\n{{s-end}}\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-inc}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Parthasarathy, Kolusu}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Telugu politicians]]\n[[Category:People from Krishna district]]\n[[Category:YSR Congress Party]]\n[[Category:1965 births]]\n", "name_user": "Vipinahir", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eEarly life", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kolusu_Parthasarathy"}
{"title_page": "Caroline Janvier", "text_new": "{{short description|French politician}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use British English|date = March 2020}}\n{{infobox officeholder\n| name                = Caroline Janvier\n| office              = Member of the [[National Assembly (France)|National Assembly]] for [[Loiret]]'s [[Loiret's 2nd constituency|2nd constituency]]\n| term_start          = 21 June 2017\n| image               = Caroline Janvier.jpg\n| term_end            = \n| predecessor         = [[Serge Grouard]]\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1982|03|09|df=yes}}\n| birth_place         = [[Nantes]], France\n| nationality         = French\n| party               = [[La R\u00e9publique En Marche!]]\n| alma_mater          = [[Sciences Po]]\n}}\n\n'''Caroline Janvier''' (born 9 March 1982) is a French politician from the [[La R\u00e9publique En Marche!]] party. She was elected to the [[National Assembly (France)|French National Assembly]] on 18 June 2017, representing the [[Departments of France|department]] of [[Loiret]]'s [[Loiret's 2nd constituency|second constituency]].<ref name=\"Bio\">{{Cite web|url=http://elections.interieur.gouv.fr/legislatives-2017/045/04502.html |title=Elections l\u00e9gislatives 2017 |accessdate=19 June 2017 |work=Ministry of the Interior |language=French}}</ref>\n\n== Studies ==\nCaroline Janvier studied in the French city of [[Tours]] (Indre-et-Loire) before joining a literary [[Classe pr\u00e9paratoire aux grandes \u00e9coles|preparatory class]] at the Jules Ferry highschool (Paris) then [[Sciences Po|SciencesPo Paris]] on the Dijon campus.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2017/jun/03/macron-french-france-voters-elections-en-marche|title=Macron\u2019s fresh faces introduce themselves to France\u2019s voters|last=Willsher|first=Kim|date=3 June 2017|work=The Observer|access-date=14 January 2020|language=en-GB|issn=0029-7712}}</ref>\n\n== Professional career ==\nAfter her graduation at SciencesPo, she works during one year and a half in [[Kenya]] for the French Ministry of Economics and Finance, to establish relationships between French insurance companies and Eastern African banks. After that, she settles in the [[Loiret]] department to work in social affairs.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.francebleu.fr/infos/politique/legislatives-qui-est-caroline-janvier-la-nouvelle-deputee-en-marche-de-la-2e-circonscription-du-loiret-1497518538|title=L\u00e9gislatives : qui est Caroline Janvier, la nouvelle d\u00e9put\u00e9e En Marche ! de la 2e circonscription du Loiret ?|date=18 June 2017|website=France Bleu|language=fr|access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nDuring six years, she works at the Aidaphi association (Association Interd\u00e9partementale pour le D\u00e9veloppement des Actions en faveur des Personnes Handicap\u00e9es et Inadapt\u00e9es) as technical adviser, where she negotiates financial resources with the relevant public authorities (ARS, departmental council, etc.), manages the association's law monitoring and follows the various establishments and services of the association. She also works as independent consultant for various consulting firms in the medical and social sector.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://carolinejanvier.fr/a-propos/|title=Biographie \u2013 Caroline Janvier \u2013 D\u00e9put\u00e9e du Loiret, 2\u00e8me circonscription|language=fr-FR|access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Member of Parliament ==\nShe joins [[La R\u00e9publique En Marche!|En Marche !]] from its beginning in April 2016 and becomes its candidate for the [[2017 French legislative election]]s to replace the party's departmental point of contact Emmanuel Constantin when he was found ineligible due to his professional activity.\n\nOn 18 June 2017, Caroline Janvier is elected Member of the [[National Assembly (France)|National Assembly]] for the Loiret's second constituency, winning by 51,23% on the election's second round, facing the former [[The Republicans (France)|Les R\u00e9publicains]] MP Serge Grouard.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.interieur.gouv.fr/Elections/Les-resultats/Legislatives/elecresult__legislatives-2017|title=R\u00e9sultats des \u00e9lections l\u00e9gislatives 2017|last=l'Int\u00e9rieur|first=Minist\u00e8re de|website=interieur.gouv.fr/Elections/Les-resultats/Legislatives/elecresult__legislatives-2017|language=fr-FR|access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.francebleu.fr/infos/politique/legislatives-qui-est-caroline-janvier-la-nouvelle-deputee-en-marche-de-la-2e-circonscription-du-loiret-1497518538|title=L\u00e9gislatives : qui est Caroline Janvier, la nouvelle d\u00e9put\u00e9e En Marche ! de la 2e circonscription du Loiret ?|date=18 June 2017|website=France Bleu|language=fr|access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn Parliament, she is a member of the Social Affairs commission as well as of the European Affairs commission. She is the President of the France-Russia parliamentary friendship group and is a member of the [[Inter-Parliamentary Union|Interparliamentary Union]]'s French delegation. She becomes Vice-President of the information mission on the revision of [[bioethics]] laws before joining the special commission on the 2019 law on bioethics.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www2.assemblee-nationale.fr/deputes/fiche/OMC_PA720074|title=Mme Caroline Janvier - Loiret (2e circonscription) - Assembl\u00e9e nationale|website=www2.assemblee-nationale.fr|access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nAs a specialist in disability and inclusion, Caroline Janvier is the author of an amendment in the PACTE law on the French economy. The amendment's aim is to create a \"Handicap\" label for the companies most involved in including disabled workers in their human resources and to increase employment's accessibility for disabled citizens.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://france3-regions.francetvinfo.fr/centre-val-de-loire/loiret/creation-label-handicap-entreprises-caroline-janvier-deputee-du-loiret-explique-quoi-ca-consiste-1643210.html|title=Cr\u00e9ation d'un label handicap pour les entreprises : le point avec Caroline Janvier, d\u00e9put\u00e9e du Loiret|website=France 3 Centre-Val de Loire|language=fr|access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://informations.handicap.fr/a-label-handicap-entreprises-11692.php|title=Handicap : bient\u00f4t un label pour les entreprises engag\u00e9es ?|last=Handicap.fr|website=Handicap.fr|language=fr|access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2019, she publishes an information report on the [[Environmental policy of the European Union|European Union's plastics strategy]], together with the Les R\u00e9publicains MP Bernard Deflesselles.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.assemblee-nationale.fr/15/europe/rap-info/i2132.asp|title=N\u00b0\u00a02132 - Rapport d'information de Mme Caroline Janvier et M. Bernard Deflesselles d\u00e9pos\u00e9 par la commission des affaires europ\u00e9ennes sur la strat\u00e9gie europ\u00e9enne sur les mati\u00e8res plastiques|website=assemblee-nationale.fr|access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref> Since the end of 2019, she is working as a rapporteur on another European Affairs' information report focusing on the [[European Neighbourhood Policy]], together with the Socialist MP Joaquim Pueyo.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://lepetitjournal.com/tunis/actualites/politique-europeenne-de-voisinage-visite-officielle-larp-270575|title=POLITIQUE EUROPEENNE DE VOISINAGE - Visite officielle \u00e0 l'ARP|website=lepetitjournal.com|language=fr|access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 14 January 2020, she becomes thematical rapporteur on recreational [[Cannabis (drug)|cannabis]] in the National Assembly's common information mission on the regulation and impact of the different uses of cannabis.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www2.assemblee-nationale.fr/deputes/fiche/OMC_PA720074|title=Mme Caroline Janvier - Loiret (2e circonscription) - Assembl\u00e9e nationale|website=www2.assemblee-nationale.fr|access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[2017 French legislative election]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Janvier, Caroline}}\n[[Category:1982 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Deputies of the 15th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic]]\n[[Category:La R\u00e9publique En Marche politicians]]\n[[Category:People from Nantes]]\n[[Category:Politicians from Pays de la Loire]]\n[[Category:Sciences Po alumni]]\n[[Category:Women members of the National Assembly (France)]]\n[[Category:21st-century French women politicians]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|French politician}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Use British English|date = March 2020}}\n{{infobox officeholder\n| name                = Caroline Janvier\n| office              = Member of the [[National Assembly (France)|National Assembly]] for [[Loiret]]'s [[Loiret's 2nd constituency|2nd constituency]]\n| term_start          = 21 June 2017\n| image               = Caroline Janvier.jpg\n| term_end            = \n| predecessor         = [[Serge Grouard]]\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1982|03|09|df=yes}}\n| birth_place         = [[Nantes]], France\n| nationality         = French\n| party               = [[La R\u00e9publique En Marche!]]\n| alma_mater          = [[Sciences Po]]\n}}\n\n'''Caroline Janvier''' (born 9 March 1982) is a French politician from the [[La R\u00e9publique En Marche!]] party. She was elected to the [[National Assembly (France)|French National Assembly]] on 18 June 2017, representing the [[Departments of France|department]] of [[Loiret]]'s [[Loiret's 2nd constituency|second constituency]].<ref name=\"Bio\">{{Cite web|url=http://elections.interieur.gouv.fr/legislatives-2017/045/04502.html |title=Elections l\u00e9gislatives 2017 |accessdate=19 June 2017 |work=Ministry of the Interior |language=French}}</ref>\n\n== Studies ==\nCaroline Janvier studied in the French city of [[Tours]] (Indre-et-Loire) before joining a literary [[Classe pr\u00e9paratoire aux grandes \u00e9coles|preparatory class]] at the Jules Ferry highschool (Paris) then [[Sciences Po|SciencesPo Paris]] on the Dijon campus.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2017/jun/03/macron-french-france-voters-elections-en-marche|title=Macron\u2019s fresh faces introduce themselves to France\u2019s voters|last=Willsher|first=Kim|date=3 June 2017|work=The Observer|access-date=14 January 2020|language=en-GB|issn=0029-7712}}</ref>\n\n== Professional career ==\nAfter her graduation at SciencesPo, she works during one year and a half in [[Kenya]] for the French Ministry of Economics and Finance, to establish relationships between French insurance companies and Eastern African banks. After that, she settles in the [[Loiret]] department to work in social affairs.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.francebleu.fr/infos/politique/legislatives-qui-est-caroline-janvier-la-nouvelle-deputee-en-marche-de-la-2e-circonscription-du-loiret-1497518538|title=L\u00e9gislatives : qui est Caroline Janvier, la nouvelle d\u00e9put\u00e9e En Marche ! de la 2e circonscription du Loiret ?|date=18 June 2017|website=France Bleu|language=fr|access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nDuring six years, she works at the Aidaphi association (Association Interd\u00e9partementale pour le D\u00e9veloppement des Actions en faveur des Personnes Handicap\u00e9es et Inadapt\u00e9es) as technical adviser, where she negotiates financial resources with the relevant public authorities (ARS, departmental council, etc.), manages the association's law monitoring and follows the various establishments and services of the association. She also works as independent consultant for various consulting firms in the medical and social sector.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://carolinejanvier.fr/a-propos/|title=Biographie \u2013 Caroline Janvier \u2013 D\u00e9put\u00e9e du Loiret, 2\u00e8me circonscription|language=fr-FR|access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Member of Parliament ==\nShe joins [[La R\u00e9publique En Marche!|En Marche !]] from its beginning in April 2016 and becomes its candidate for the [[2017 French legislative election]]s to replace the party's departmental point of contact Emmanuel Constantin when he was found ineligible due to his professional activity.\n\nOn 18 June 2017, Caroline Janvier is elected Member of the [[National Assembly (France)|National Assembly]] for the Loiret's second constituency, winning by 51,23% on the election's second round, facing the former [[The Republicans (France)|Les R\u00e9publicains]] MP Serge Grouard.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.interieur.gouv.fr/Elections/Les-resultats/Legislatives/elecresult__legislatives-2017|title=R\u00e9sultats des \u00e9lections l\u00e9gislatives 2017|last=l'Int\u00e9rieur|first=Minist\u00e8re de|website=interieur.gouv.fr/Elections/Les-resultats/Legislatives/elecresult__legislatives-2017|language=fr-FR|access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.francebleu.fr/infos/politique/legislatives-qui-est-caroline-janvier-la-nouvelle-deputee-en-marche-de-la-2e-circonscription-du-loiret-1497518538|title=L\u00e9gislatives : qui est Caroline Janvier, la nouvelle d\u00e9put\u00e9e En Marche ! de la 2e circonscription du Loiret ?|date=18 June 2017|website=France Bleu|language=fr|access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn Parliament, she is a member of the Social Affairs commission as well as of the European Affairs commission. She is the President of the France-Russia parliamentary friendship group and is a member of the [[Inter-Parliamentary Union|Interparliamentary Union]]'s French delegation. She becomes Vice-President of the information mission on the revision of [[bioethics]] laws before joining the special commission on the 2019 law on bioethics.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www2.assemblee-nationale.fr/deputes/fiche/OMC_PA720074|title=Mme Caroline Janvier - Loiret (2e circonscription) - Assembl\u00e9e nationale|website=www2.assemblee-nationale.fr|access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nAs a specialist in disability and inclusion, Caroline Janvier is the author of an amendment in the PACTE law on the French economy. The amendment's aim is to create a \"Handicap\" label for the companies most involved in including disabled workers in their human resources and to increase employment's accessibility for disabled citizens.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://france3-regions.francetvinfo.fr/centre-val-de-loire/loiret/creation-label-handicap-entreprises-caroline-janvier-deputee-du-loiret-explique-quoi-ca-consiste-1643210.html|title=Cr\u00e9ation d'un label handicap pour les entreprises : le point avec Caroline Janvier, d\u00e9put\u00e9e du Loiret|website=France 3 Centre-Val de Loire|language=fr|access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://informations.handicap.fr/a-label-handicap-entreprises-11692.php|title=Handicap : bient\u00f4t un label pour les entreprises engag\u00e9es ?|last=Handicap.fr|website=Handicap.fr|language=fr|access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2019, she publishes an information report on the [[Environmental policy of the European Union|European Union's plastics strategy]], together with the Les R\u00e9publicains MP Bernard Deflesselles.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.assemblee-nationale.fr/15/europe/rap-info/i2132.asp|title=N\u00b0\u00a02132 - Rapport d'information de Mme Caroline Janvier et M. Bernard Deflesselles d\u00e9pos\u00e9 par la commission des affaires europ\u00e9ennes sur la strat\u00e9gie europ\u00e9enne sur les mati\u00e8res plastiques|website=assemblee-nationale.fr|access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref> Since the end of 2019, she is working as a rapporteur on another European Affairs' information report focusing on the [[European Neighbourhood Policy]], together with the Socialist MP Joaquim Pueyo.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://lepetitjournal.com/tunis/actualites/politique-europeenne-de-voisinage-visite-officielle-larp-270575|title=POLITIQUE EUROPEENNE DE VOISINAGE - Visite officielle \u00e0 l'ARP|website=lepetitjournal.com|language=fr|access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 14 January 2020, she becomes thematical rapporteur on recreational [[Cannabis (drug)|cannabis]] in the National Assembly's common information mission on the regulation and impact of the different uses of cannabis.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www2.assemblee-nationale.fr/deputes/fiche/OMC_PA720074|title=Mme Caroline Janvier - Loiret (2e circonscription) - Assembl\u00e9e nationale|website=www2.assemblee-nationale.fr|access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[2017 French legislative election]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Janvier, Caroline}}\n[[Category:1982 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Deputies of the 15th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic]]\n[[Category:La R\u00e9publique En Marche politicians]]\n[[Category:People from Nantes]]\n[[Category:Politicians from Pays de la Loire]]\n[[Category:Sciences Po alumni]]\n[[Category:Women members of the National Assembly (France)]]\n[[Category:21st-century French women politicians]]\n", "name_user": "Lugnuts", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Caroline_Janvier"}
